HEADWORD: Coontie
<hw>Coon"tie</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
cycadaceous plant of Florida and the West Indies, the <spn>Zamia
integrifolia</spn>, from the stems of which a kind of sago is
prepared.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

